00:04:30.199 --> 00:04:32.201
by so many and why it was so

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:36.062
easy for Christianity to tear him down.

00:04:37.023 --> 00:04:39.463
He made that possible,

00:04:39.483 --> 00:04:40.903
which I think is the greatest grief of

00:04:40.983 --> 00:04:41.704
all to God,

00:04:41.964 --> 00:04:45.026
knowing what would happen as a result of

00:04:45.065 --> 00:04:45.326
this.

00:04:45.406 --> 00:04:47.226
And God chose not to cover it up.

00:04:47.867 --> 00:04:48.887
He wanted it revealed.

00:04:48.947 --> 00:04:49.608
He revealed it.

00:04:50.447 --> 00:04:51.769
And so we're going to deal with it.

00:04:53.442 --> 00:04:56.584
other reason is uh of course that in

00:04:56.644 --> 00:04:59.266
Judaism and Christianity the excuse for

00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:02.309
their replacement messiahs are it's all

00:05:02.348 --> 00:05:05.692
based on this event we don't give that

00:05:06.012 --> 00:05:11.257
more credibility by presenting the basis

00:05:11.297 --> 00:05:18.182
for it but we look like cowards if

00:05:18.221 --> 00:05:19.142
we can't deal with it um

00:05:22.170 --> 00:05:25.810
we are never gonna run from something.

00:05:25.971 --> 00:05:29.812
And ultimately it is the timing that is

00:05:29.851 --> 00:05:35.752
so vital to us because when we returned

00:05:35.892 --> 00:05:38.394
to the narrative in the garden and we

00:05:38.434 --> 00:05:40.694
realized that God caused the fall of man

00:05:41.274 --> 00:05:44.636
and then realized the things that God

00:05:44.755 --> 00:05:48.336
expressly stated that he was expecting

00:05:48.377 --> 00:05:49.697
from us, wanting from us,

00:05:50.850 --> 00:05:53.192
to release us from this planet so that

00:05:53.211 --> 00:05:55.233
we could experience the universe with him.

00:05:56.913 --> 00:05:59.055
We came to see,

00:05:59.235 --> 00:06:03.416
and now I've found many affirmations of

00:06:03.456 --> 00:06:07.959
the fact that God's interest is not in

00:06:08.019 --> 00:06:08.879
us being perfect.

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:11.701
There really is no Hebrew word for that

00:06:11.721 --> 00:06:12.281
concept.

00:06:12.341 --> 00:06:13.422
And when I have rendered it in the

00:06:13.442 --> 00:06:13.802
past,

00:06:14.403 --> 00:06:19.545
it is by just superficially reporting what

00:06:19.625 --> 00:06:19.846
the

00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:24.242
lexicons and Hebrew English dictionaries

00:06:24.504 --> 00:06:24.783
say,

00:06:25.283 --> 00:06:27.603
but what they say was only to echo

00:06:28.363 --> 00:06:31.425
religious terminology and religious texts.

00:06:32.904 --> 00:06:35.485
The word tamym Dowdsn't mean perfect.

00:06:37.045 --> 00:06:38.605
It's based on tamam, the verb,

00:06:39.365 --> 00:06:40.887
and it means to complete the job,

00:06:41.726 --> 00:06:44.247
to finish what one starts,

00:06:45.067 --> 00:06:47.367
to fulfill what needs to be accomplished.

00:06:48.353 --> 00:06:49.694
And Dowd did those things.

00:06:49.995 --> 00:06:51.557
And because he did those things,

00:06:51.596 --> 00:06:53.939
he is tamym.

00:06:55.199 --> 00:06:57.721
And therefore, he was qualified.

00:06:57.742 --> 00:07:00.423
For the very reason he got back up

00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:01.384
and got going again.

00:07:02.084 --> 00:07:04.387
So there is a happily ever after ending

00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:05.408
to this story.

00:07:05.887 --> 00:07:08.110
But for the story to be real,

00:07:09.370 --> 00:07:11.632
it has some gut-wrenching details.

00:07:12.254 --> 00:07:16.276
And this is all part of them.

00:07:18.122 --> 00:07:22.728
So now after we have learned that Dowd

00:07:24.209 --> 00:07:25.410
was sleeping during the day,

00:07:27.713 --> 00:07:31.355
abusing alcohol,

00:07:31.375 --> 00:07:33.437
turned into a voyeur at night,

00:07:37.781 --> 00:07:39.963
determined that a woman that he thought

00:07:39.983 --> 00:07:42.565
was pretty belonged to another man and

00:07:42.685 --> 00:07:43.786
abducted her anyway,

00:07:44.266 --> 00:07:46.168
and then immediately had sex with her,

00:07:46.209 --> 00:07:48.310
which happens to be the textbook

00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:49.331
definition of rape.

00:07:52.052 --> 00:07:54.355
The fact that he then tried to cover

00:07:54.394 --> 00:07:56.776
it up and was gluttonous in the process.

00:07:58.237 --> 00:08:03.622
The fact that he had a man assassinated

00:08:04.041 --> 00:08:05.944
and then turned his general into a

00:08:06.004 --> 00:08:07.485
co-conspirator in murder.

00:08:09.711 --> 00:08:12.192
the level of depravity that was in the

00:08:12.213 --> 00:08:18.716
letter that he wrote to Yow'ab to get

00:08:19.677 --> 00:08:21.278
the light of Yah extinguished.

00:08:21.298 --> 00:08:22.978
That was the man's name, 'Uwryah.

00:08:24.620 --> 00:08:27.742
It's, quite frankly, it's debilitating.

00:08:29.283 --> 00:08:30.824
So here's how the story continues.

00:08:30.863 --> 00:08:32.806
We're in the twenty-sixth statement of the

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:34.567
eleventh chapter of Second Samuel,

00:08:34.586 --> 00:08:35.606
means to listen to God.

00:08:36.327 --> 00:08:37.469
The wife of 'Uwryah

00:08:38.206 --> 00:08:40.106
heard that her Ba'al, her husband,

00:08:41.427 --> 00:08:43.268
the Light of Yah, perished.

