00:09:27.836 --> 00:09:33.476
She had a child around him, a son.

00:09:33.517 --> 00:09:35.298
But from the perspective of Yahowah,

00:09:36.283 --> 00:09:36.722
Dowd,

00:09:37.143 --> 00:09:39.543
remember I told you to recall this word

00:09:39.724 --> 00:09:41.004
as a verb, raa'?

00:09:43.524 --> 00:09:45.585
But from the perspective of Yahowah, Dowd,

00:09:45.664 --> 00:09:48.905
raa', had consistently been wrong.

00:09:50.606 --> 00:09:53.307
He had habitually been distressing and

00:09:53.346 --> 00:09:53.767
harmful,

00:09:55.148 --> 00:09:58.187
even evil in the things he had said

00:09:58.227 --> 00:10:02.909
and done.

00:10:02.970 --> 00:10:04.529
Second Samuel, eleven, twenty-seven.

00:10:06.195 --> 00:10:10.197
So if you think that I'm overstepping my

00:10:10.256 --> 00:10:12.518
bounds and criticizing our king,

00:10:13.717 --> 00:10:16.340
you can never be wrong if your conclusions

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:20.160
match those of Yahowah.

