But at least I know that I'm in

00:10:40.865 --> 00:10:43.168
good company and correctly processing the

00:10:43.227 --> 00:10:45.830
evidence when Yahowah concurs.

00:10:47.532 --> 00:10:47.951
Moreover,

00:10:48.111 --> 00:10:51.955
I'm rather certain that what I've already

00:10:52.034 --> 00:10:57.740
said to his face and will say is

00:10:57.860 --> 00:11:00.062
far beyond what I've shared here.

00:11:03.375 --> 00:11:06.736
Just as Dowd told Yow'ab that there would

00:11:06.777 --> 00:11:10.038
be no perception of raa', wrongdoing,

00:11:11.758 --> 00:11:12.817
Yahowah said otherwise,

00:11:13.717 --> 00:11:15.318
that the whole rotten affair had been

00:11:15.399 --> 00:11:17.519
raa', despicable from the outset.

00:11:18.379 --> 00:11:20.679
And let's be clear, Bathsheba,

00:11:21.519 --> 00:11:22.379
she is no Ammah.

00:11:22.399 --> 00:11:22.440
So,

00:11:26.360 --> 00:11:28.961
guess who were no longer on speaking

00:11:29.001 --> 00:11:29.361
terms?

00:11:30.626 --> 00:11:31.048
Yep,

00:11:31.067 --> 00:11:34.650
Yahowah delivered his condemnation of his

00:11:34.750 --> 00:11:42.157
son via an intermediary.

00:11:42.216 --> 00:11:47.341
When Yahowah sent Nathan,

00:11:47.400 --> 00:11:49.842
Nathan means gift, to Dowd,

00:11:50.082 --> 00:11:50.943
which means beloved.

00:11:52.865 --> 00:11:54.307
He came to him and he said to

00:11:54.346 --> 00:11:54.506
him,

00:11:55.993 --> 00:11:59.033
There were two individuals in a particular

00:11:59.073 --> 00:12:01.835
city, one rich and powerful,

00:12:02.894 --> 00:12:03.934
and the other one was poor.

00:12:05.615 --> 00:12:08.736
This is the beginning of second Samuel,

00:12:08.817 --> 00:12:10.956
the first verse.

00:12:11.876 --> 00:12:14.197
The exceedingly wealthy one had

00:12:15.018 --> 00:12:18.918
excessively large flocks of sheep,

00:12:18.979 --> 00:12:21.179
as well as herds of cattle.

00:12:23.833 --> 00:12:26.255
The poor person had nothing except one

00:12:26.655 --> 00:12:30.438
little lamb, an insignificant ewe,

00:12:31.639 --> 00:12:32.659
which he had acquired,

00:12:33.760 --> 00:12:36.143
and he sustained and nurtured her life.

00:12:37.082 --> 00:12:37.923
She grew up with him,

00:12:38.784 --> 00:12:43.687
becoming tremendously valuable to him,

00:12:43.727 --> 00:12:46.450
even appreciated by his children.

00:12:49.106 --> 00:12:52.450
When together, a morsel of his food,

00:12:52.990 --> 00:12:56.794
just crumbs and scraps of his, she ate.

00:12:58.417 --> 00:13:02.341
She even drank from his cup.

00:13:02.380 --> 00:13:04.682
She would lie down and rest in his

00:13:04.842 --> 00:13:07.806
arms.

00:13:07.865 --> 00:13:09.427
She became like a daughter to him.

00:13:12.634 --> 00:13:15.316
A visitor who was traveling came to the

00:13:15.395 --> 00:13:16.817
rich and powerful man,

00:13:17.197 --> 00:13:19.557
but he showed no compassion and was

00:13:19.677 --> 00:13:22.279
unwilling to take one of the lambs in

00:13:22.340 --> 00:13:25.662
his flock or cattle from his herd to

00:13:25.701 --> 00:13:28.202
do something for the traveler who had come

00:13:28.264 --> 00:13:28.604
to him.

00:13:30.664 --> 00:13:31.164
Instead,

00:13:32.785 --> 00:13:36.168
he grasped hold of and took the ewe

00:13:36.808 --> 00:13:39.769
of the poor person and prepared it for

00:13:39.809 --> 00:13:42.172
the man who had come to him.

00:13:46.732 --> 00:13:49.693
I'll note to self and to all who

00:13:49.754 --> 00:13:50.235
are listening,

00:13:50.855 --> 00:13:52.796
don't ever try to match wits with Yah.

00:13:54.255 --> 00:13:56.837
There was no wiggling out of this.

00:13:57.817 --> 00:14:00.298
But what's amazing to me is the empathy

00:14:00.599 --> 00:14:04.701
Yahowah expressed and the extent that he

00:14:04.740 --> 00:14:07.322
went to to teach his wayward son a

00:14:07.381 --> 00:14:10.903
lesson, one that he might understand,

00:14:11.703 --> 00:14:13.725
although at this point he didn't.

00:14:16.677 --> 00:14:17.418
As for Nathan,

00:14:18.818 --> 00:14:22.240
he is announcing the gift of Dowd,

00:14:22.659 --> 00:14:23.561
the beloved son,

00:14:24.801 --> 00:14:27.922
given in Yeshayah nine to redeem mankind's

00:14:27.961 --> 00:14:29.682
fractured relationship with God.

00:14:29.743 --> 00:14:32.683
So by that time, this had been resolved.

00:14:32.764 --> 00:14:36.164
It just wouldn't be resolved for many

00:14:36.205 --> 00:14:39.365
years after this transpired.

00:14:41.427 --> 00:14:44.207
Dowd would be the lamb

00:14:45.409 --> 00:14:49.811
And the one sharing this with you is

00:14:49.850 --> 00:14:50.230
the bull.

00:14:52.611 --> 00:14:54.892
Working together and collaboratively with

00:14:54.951 --> 00:14:57.153
Yahowah, once resolving this mess,

00:14:57.212 --> 00:15:01.193
we foster reconciliation during the Miqra'ey

00:15:01.214 --> 00:15:04.534
of Pesach and then on Taruw'ah.

00:15:07.475 --> 00:15:09.796
The emotional portrayal of the lone lamb,

00:15:09.895 --> 00:15:12.197
one acquired when it was very young.

00:15:13.958 --> 00:15:15.500
then nurtured and sustained,

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:18.061
becoming a beloved child,

00:15:19.120 --> 00:15:21.562
cradled in the arms of the one who

00:15:21.601 --> 00:15:22.082
adored it.

00:15:24.123 --> 00:15:26.705
In the presence of a grateful family,

00:15:28.184 --> 00:15:32.687
who was then taken away and prepared to

00:15:32.706 --> 00:15:35.408
meet the needs of a newly arrived guest,

00:15:37.229 --> 00:15:37.649
of course,

00:15:37.688 --> 00:15:40.049
is a portrait of Dowd's eventual

00:15:40.110 --> 00:15:41.291
fulfillment of Passover.

00:15:43.783 --> 00:15:47.104
When the man, when he, I should say,

00:15:47.144 --> 00:15:47.744
man's up,

00:15:48.104 --> 00:15:49.864
accepts his place and shows some

00:15:49.923 --> 00:15:51.043
compassion for others,

00:15:53.345 --> 00:15:57.904
he will be that lamb.

00:15:58.024 --> 00:16:02.225
And then for those who prefer hindsight to

00:16:02.285 --> 00:16:02.885
foresight,

00:16:04.167 --> 00:16:07.287
the emblematic of the validation of the

00:16:07.346 --> 00:16:09.647
covenant narrative with Yitschaq and

00:16:09.726 --> 00:16:10.207
Abraham.

00:16:11.048 --> 00:16:12.067
Remember they ascended?

00:16:13.179 --> 00:16:17.120
Mowryah to celebrate Passover right here on

00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:18.620
the same place on Mowryah,

00:16:19.240 --> 00:16:23.042
albeit one thousand years earlier at the

00:16:23.081 --> 00:16:26.243
time when Yahowah promised that he would

00:16:26.283 --> 00:16:26.982
provide the lamb.

00:16:29.863 --> 00:16:32.323
Well, that was enduring and brilliant.

00:16:32.543 --> 00:16:35.445
I'm bewildered that Dowd was so slow on

00:16:35.485 --> 00:16:36.144
the uptake.

00:16:36.424 --> 00:16:37.424
But then again,

00:16:38.605 --> 00:16:41.365
I suppose that his mindset was different

00:16:41.426 --> 00:16:42.245
at the moment and

00:16:43.413 --> 00:16:46.254
We benefit from knowing how the entire

00:16:46.315 --> 00:16:48.236
story plays out over the next three

00:16:48.277 --> 00:16:48.716
millennia,

00:16:48.758 --> 00:16:51.419
which he did not process at this time.

00:16:52.721 --> 00:16:55.383
So this was the second occasion in so

00:16:55.403 --> 00:16:58.485
many words that we have been told that

00:16:59.446 --> 00:17:01.288
Dowd had a wicked temper.

00:17:02.849 --> 00:17:08.854
It is part and parcel to being impulsive.

00:17:08.874 --> 00:17:09.634
So it's temper.

00:17:09.934 --> 00:17:10.675
It was inflamed.

00:17:11.457 --> 00:17:13.657
And his rage was aroused tremendously

00:17:13.698 --> 00:17:16.038
against the man.

00:17:16.058 --> 00:17:18.799
Then he said to Nathan, as Yahowah lives,

00:17:18.880 --> 00:17:23.342
surely the son who did this deserves to

00:17:23.402 --> 00:17:25.323
die.

00:17:25.442 --> 00:17:26.563
And in addition,

00:17:26.603 --> 00:17:29.544
he must restore the lamb and repay

00:17:29.604 --> 00:17:33.086
fourfold his as recompense because he did

00:17:33.105 --> 00:17:33.605
this thing.

00:17:35.067 --> 00:17:38.208
And also because he had no compassion.

00:17:43.731 --> 00:17:48.292
Then Nathan said to Dowd you are that

00:17:48.353 --> 00:17:57.435
man.

00:17:57.496 --> 00:18:00.557
At the moment you could have heard a

00:18:00.596 --> 00:18:04.179
snowflake fall.

00:18:04.199 --> 00:18:07.019
The silence between these men and their

00:18:07.038 --> 00:18:08.599
God would have been deafening.

00:18:10.026 --> 00:18:10.665
And of course,

00:18:10.766 --> 00:18:12.968
we would do well to consider the

00:18:13.028 --> 00:18:16.869
expressions on the faces and thoughts now

00:18:17.609 --> 00:18:20.771
whirling in the minds of the gift and

00:18:20.811 --> 00:18:21.451
of the beloved.

00:18:23.133 --> 00:18:23.593
Frankly,

00:18:23.633 --> 00:18:27.694
while Nathan's lips were moving and words

00:18:27.734 --> 00:18:29.135
were spilling out of his mouth,

00:18:30.135 --> 00:18:33.137
I Dowd Dowd processed any more than the

00:18:33.178 --> 00:18:35.219
first and last statement of what follows.

00:18:38.019 --> 00:18:38.300
Thus,

00:18:39.559 --> 00:18:42.540
says Yahowah, the God of Yisrael.

00:18:44.301 --> 00:18:45.682
I anointed you, Mashyach,

00:18:45.722 --> 00:18:47.123
to be king over Yisrael.

00:18:48.443 --> 00:18:50.384
I rescued and delivered you from the hand

00:18:50.424 --> 00:18:51.125
of Sha'uwl.

00:18:51.305 --> 00:18:53.865
I gave to you the house of your

00:18:53.986 --> 00:18:54.906
Adon, your Lord,

00:18:55.707 --> 00:18:58.807
and your Lord's women into your lap.

00:18:59.749 --> 00:19:02.430
And I gave you the house of Yisrael

00:19:03.431 --> 00:19:04.391
and that of Yahuwdah.

00:19:05.952 --> 00:19:07.513
And if this were too little,

00:19:08.134 --> 00:19:09.894
this were insufficient for you,

00:19:11.375 --> 00:19:12.375
I would have added to it,

00:19:13.375 --> 00:19:15.656
giving you the like of it.

00:19:17.478 --> 00:19:23.101
And so much more.

00:19:23.141 --> 00:19:27.343
Forty eight years prior to this stern

00:19:27.403 --> 00:19:28.022
admonishment.

00:19:29.743 --> 00:19:32.226
Yahowah had not only anointed Dowd as the

00:19:32.246 --> 00:19:36.347
Messiah and appointed him the future king

00:19:36.387 --> 00:19:37.108
of Israel.

00:19:38.048 --> 00:19:42.771
He had given his beloved his spirit.

00:19:42.791 --> 00:19:45.594
God had chosen a young lamb and he

00:19:45.753 --> 00:19:50.376
nurtured and raised him as his son.

00:19:50.457 --> 00:19:54.380
He is entrusting his people to him.

00:19:57.792 --> 00:20:00.273
The fight for validation and supremacy

00:20:00.334 --> 00:20:03.994
between the Benjamite Sha'uwl and the Yahuwd

00:20:04.035 --> 00:20:07.055
Dowd is among the most unheralded of all

00:20:08.215 --> 00:20:09.195
prophetic portrayals.

00:20:10.476 --> 00:20:13.257
It is analogous to the Benjamite,

00:20:13.297 --> 00:20:14.596
of course, by the same name,

00:20:15.096 --> 00:20:18.817
the one who was also demon-possessed and

00:20:19.458 --> 00:20:21.638
who not only wanted Dowd to dead and

00:20:21.679 --> 00:20:22.179
buried,

00:20:22.878 --> 00:20:24.759
but was willing to misappropriate the

00:20:24.799 --> 00:20:25.119
Towrah.

00:20:26.020 --> 00:20:31.244
to achieve his deadly schemes.

00:20:31.285 --> 00:20:34.606
This is the battle of the ages that

00:20:34.647 --> 00:20:38.450
Yahowah is discussing between man's most

00:20:38.490 --> 00:20:40.291
popular religion and the relationship

00:20:40.332 --> 00:20:43.374
Yahowah sought to achieve through his son.

00:20:45.715 --> 00:20:48.458
And God has taken sides against

00:20:48.518 --> 00:20:50.799
Christianity and in support of the

00:20:50.839 --> 00:20:51.160
covenant.

00:20:53.903 --> 00:20:56.604
Yahowah is just not in the business of

00:20:56.644 --> 00:20:57.584
accommodating men.

00:20:58.384 --> 00:21:02.045
In the dissertation upon the exit from

00:21:02.144 --> 00:21:02.384
Eden,

00:21:02.884 --> 00:21:05.625
he made it unambiguously clear that we

00:21:05.645 --> 00:21:07.287
would have to work to survive.

00:21:08.326 --> 00:21:09.027
But occasionally,

00:21:09.666 --> 00:21:10.708
God will make an exception,

00:21:10.827 --> 00:21:13.887
at least to the extent that he will

00:21:14.348 --> 00:21:18.569
augment what his covenant children could

00:21:18.609 --> 00:21:19.930
achieve independently.

00:21:21.029 --> 00:21:22.090
He will do this

00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:27.150
so that we have the time and resources

00:21:27.190 --> 00:21:30.092
to pursue the family business.

00:21:30.152 --> 00:21:33.054
So Dowd was the supreme beneficiary of

00:21:33.074 --> 00:21:35.015
this arrangement, the ultimate exemplar.

00:21:35.055 --> 00:21:38.758
Yahowah is affirming that he received a

00:21:38.857 --> 00:21:41.618
palatial home filled with women to keep

00:21:41.659 --> 00:21:42.319
him company.

00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:46.622
But he was also afforded his father's most

00:21:47.222 --> 00:21:52.445
valued treasure, Yisrael and Yahuwdah.

00:21:56.040 --> 00:21:58.981
Having tried it himself and been so

00:21:59.182 --> 00:22:00.301
soundly rejected,

00:22:01.041 --> 00:22:03.762
God was keenly aware that there is no

00:22:03.823 --> 00:22:07.182
more difficult job than representing him

00:22:07.303 --> 00:22:08.324
and speaking for him.

00:22:09.943 --> 00:22:13.025
Moshe was eminently qualified and

00:22:13.204 --> 00:22:14.545
marvelously supported,

00:22:15.704 --> 00:22:17.404
but he didn't make it through the first

00:22:17.424 --> 00:22:20.665
year before he was, well,

00:22:20.726 --> 00:22:23.326
that he snapped and he begged Yahowah to

00:22:23.446 --> 00:22:24.467
relieve him from duty.

00:22:26.791 --> 00:22:28.732
Yahowah met the challenge by providing

00:22:28.792 --> 00:22:31.935
additional support and supplies.

00:22:33.356 --> 00:22:35.337
Although there were occasional missteps,

00:22:35.417 --> 00:22:37.479
Dowd managed to stay on course for

00:22:37.539 --> 00:22:40.020
forty-eight years before he opted out.

00:22:41.342 --> 00:22:44.564
In appreciation of what his son had and

00:22:44.644 --> 00:22:45.345
would achieve,

00:22:46.185 --> 00:22:48.106
God is not only on record saying that

00:22:48.126 --> 00:22:50.509
there was no limit on what he was

00:22:50.548 --> 00:22:51.469
willing to provide,

00:22:52.309 --> 00:22:53.871
even if it was nothing more than

00:22:53.911 --> 00:22:55.291
additional houses and women.

00:22:56.986 --> 00:22:59.205
or as valuable as his anointing,

00:22:59.267 --> 00:23:00.287
protection of people.

00:23:02.487 --> 00:23:05.127
But there is a right and a wrong

00:23:05.167 --> 00:23:08.147
way to go about this potential equation.

00:23:08.407 --> 00:23:13.369
Our Father isn't going to opt in when

00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:14.190
we opt out,

00:23:16.009 --> 00:23:18.171
nor is he going to lavish gifts upon

00:23:18.270 --> 00:23:20.851
us when we have no appreciation for their

00:23:20.911 --> 00:23:24.471
value, nor value their relationships.

00:23:25.623 --> 00:23:27.963
that makes all of this possible.

00:23:30.164 --> 00:23:32.506
We are at liberty to accept or reject

00:23:33.326 --> 00:23:34.007
the word of God.

00:23:35.047 --> 00:23:37.888
Most despise Yahowah's testimony because of

00:23:37.909 --> 00:23:40.869
course it is contrary to their religious

00:23:40.890 --> 00:23:41.390
beliefs.

00:23:42.671 --> 00:23:45.412
But that is not what is happening here

00:23:46.633 --> 00:23:49.173
because Dowd was not being religious.

00:23:51.663 --> 00:23:53.484
He isn't showing contempt for the Towrah

00:23:53.525 --> 00:23:55.826
instructions because they are in conflict

00:23:55.865 --> 00:23:58.546
with his plans to impose his authority

00:23:58.886 --> 00:23:59.666
through religion,

00:24:00.326 --> 00:24:01.867
as was the case with Paul,

00:24:02.407 --> 00:24:05.288
Akiba and Muhammad, priests,

00:24:05.348 --> 00:24:06.469
rabbis and imams.

00:24:07.390 --> 00:24:09.289
He knew what God said.

00:24:09.950 --> 00:24:12.691
He just chose to reject his Towrah guidance

00:24:13.551 --> 00:24:16.813
for the fleeting satisfaction of wine and

00:24:16.853 --> 00:24:17.133
women.

00:24:18.933 --> 00:24:19.933
God took it personally.

00:24:22.480 --> 00:24:23.060
as he should.

00:24:26.063 --> 00:24:27.963
Why, he asks,

00:24:28.804 --> 00:24:33.386
and on whose account have you despised

00:24:35.188 --> 00:24:38.710
showing such contempt for the word of

00:24:38.730 --> 00:24:44.913
Yahowah, such that you did such raw evil,

00:24:46.314 --> 00:24:47.433
wickedly troubling,

00:24:48.595 --> 00:24:50.715
and horribly wrong in his sight?

00:24:53.597 --> 00:24:57.279
You struck down the 'Uwryah,

00:24:57.519 --> 00:24:59.540
the light of Yah, the Chity,

00:24:59.621 --> 00:25:00.441
the formidable one,

00:25:02.201 --> 00:25:04.462
with the desolating sword,

00:25:06.064 --> 00:25:09.345
and his wife you have taken to be

00:25:09.404 --> 00:25:09.984
your woman.

00:25:11.125 --> 00:25:15.847
You intentionally slaughtered him with the

00:25:15.907 --> 00:25:18.308
swords of the sons of 'Amown,

00:25:19.369 --> 00:25:20.269
the son of the people.

00:25:28.537 --> 00:25:30.797
It's a choice that we're all asked to

00:25:30.836 --> 00:25:31.156
make.

00:25:32.458 --> 00:25:33.538
God's way or man's?

00:25:34.478 --> 00:25:35.617
Relationship or religion?

00:25:37.199 --> 00:25:40.638
It is the option offered long ago with

00:25:40.699 --> 00:25:44.700
the ''ets da'ath of Towb and ra.

00:25:45.700 --> 00:25:47.700
Is it not?

00:25:47.720 --> 00:25:51.181
This referendum is presented today

00:25:52.173 --> 00:25:53.553
in the word of Yahowah,

00:25:53.952 --> 00:25:55.233
also known as the Towrah.

00:25:56.294 --> 00:25:57.913
In the opening chapter of the Towrah,

00:25:57.953 --> 00:26:02.134
God revealed that Dowd would be the Gadowl

00:26:02.255 --> 00:26:05.755
Ma'or, the greater luminary.

00:26:06.276 --> 00:26:08.756
He is, as we shall soon be reminded,

00:26:08.816 --> 00:26:11.236
equated to the sun.

00:26:12.517 --> 00:26:15.416
And so by slaying 'Uwryah,

00:26:16.017 --> 00:26:19.178
Dowd extinguished the light of God on

00:26:19.298 --> 00:26:19.538
earth.

00:26:23.553 --> 00:26:27.034
The Choreb, this desolated sword,

00:26:27.233 --> 00:26:31.055
is a double entendre because it was upon

00:26:31.095 --> 00:26:31.694
the sharp,

00:26:31.795 --> 00:26:35.895
craggy summit of Mount Choreb that Moshe

00:26:36.036 --> 00:26:38.356
and the Israelites were first introduced

00:26:38.376 --> 00:26:41.038
to the Owr, the light of Yahowah.

00:26:42.337 --> 00:26:44.519
And this is when the children of Yisra'el

00:26:44.558 --> 00:26:47.078
were especially raw, malcontent,

00:26:47.118 --> 00:26:49.420
and malevolent in his sight.

00:26:51.986 --> 00:26:54.468
Always the ultimate weaver of words.

00:26:54.948 --> 00:26:58.710
With this rue originating over a woman,

00:27:00.131 --> 00:27:02.113
Yahowah would resolve it likewise.

00:27:04.153 --> 00:27:06.635
While Dowd had killed a man for her,

00:27:07.977 --> 00:27:12.199
God would save his son and the world

00:27:13.619 --> 00:27:14.161
through her.

00:27:16.221 --> 00:27:18.442
It's the ultimate contrast between the

00:27:18.663 --> 00:27:20.605
Amom, the sum of the people.

00:27:21.604 --> 00:27:24.006
and the Towrah teaching of Yahowah on behalf

00:27:24.066 --> 00:27:25.646
of the beryth, the covenant,

00:27:26.748 --> 00:27:28.848
through the Mow'edym, restoring witness.

00:27:30.269 --> 00:27:34.553
The choice between these approaches is

00:27:34.613 --> 00:27:35.373
life and death.

00:27:38.055 --> 00:27:39.756
Dowd, of course, he knew better,

00:27:40.237 --> 00:27:41.498
but he had chosen poorly.

00:27:42.377 --> 00:27:43.578
There would be a consequence.

00:27:43.618 --> 00:27:46.361
God cannot be capricious.

00:27:50.895 --> 00:27:53.057
even with his great love and favoritism

00:27:53.097 --> 00:27:56.601
for his chosen one, his anointed, his son.

00:27:58.343 --> 00:28:02.886
There must be some adherence to the rules

00:28:02.906 --> 00:28:06.711
that he had established.

00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:09.692
And so we read, Therefore, now,

00:28:11.174 --> 00:28:14.116
the sword shall never be removed from your

00:28:14.156 --> 00:28:14.597
household.

00:28:17.409 --> 00:28:20.769
Never throughout time as an 'ed,

00:28:21.529 --> 00:28:24.490
an everlasting witness as a result,

00:28:24.530 --> 00:28:29.332
because you have shown great contempt for

00:28:29.372 --> 00:28:32.192
me.

00:28:32.211 --> 00:28:36.232
Thinking so little of me that you have

00:28:36.272 --> 00:28:38.534
taken the wife of 'UwrYah,

00:28:38.594 --> 00:28:40.114
the light of y'all,

00:28:40.374 --> 00:28:43.875
the Chity formidable one to be your

00:28:43.934 --> 00:28:44.174
woman.

00:28:49.045 --> 00:28:58.807
God is saying that your perception of him

00:29:00.708 --> 00:29:07.528
was reduced to having sex with a married

00:29:07.568 --> 00:29:07.849
woman.

00:29:11.349 --> 00:29:13.871
That's how much you valued me, God said.

00:29:16.791 --> 00:29:28.538
You have shown great contempt for me.

00:29:28.598 --> 00:29:28.999
My friends,

00:29:29.038 --> 00:29:34.602
this condition would endure three

00:29:34.643 --> 00:29:36.323
millennia without respite.

00:29:36.884 --> 00:29:38.625
It's ongoing even now.

00:29:39.164 --> 00:29:40.385
It's about to get much worse.

00:29:41.843 --> 00:29:44.085
And it will not be resolved until Taruw'ah,

00:29:44.164 --> 00:29:47.067
when the bull and the goat intervene on

00:29:47.147 --> 00:29:47.667
Mowryah,

00:29:48.788 --> 00:29:50.891
and before the surviving remnant of

00:29:50.951 --> 00:29:51.652
Yisra'el.

00:29:52.853 --> 00:29:54.634
That is the lesson of the 'Ed,

00:29:54.713 --> 00:29:55.994
the eternal testimony,

00:29:57.576 --> 00:29:59.959
delivered by this restoring witness.

00:30:01.940 --> 00:30:05.042
All Yisra'el would become dead.

00:30:05.063 --> 00:30:07.065
They still are.

00:30:09.304 --> 00:30:11.846
Yisra'elites and Jews think so little of

00:30:11.885 --> 00:30:12.326
Yahowah,

00:30:13.125 --> 00:30:16.248
they've erased his name and replaced his

00:30:16.288 --> 00:30:18.108
dabarym words with their own.

00:30:19.269 --> 00:30:22.112
They continue to fight a losing battle

00:30:22.152 --> 00:30:25.053
with diminishing returns for their very

00:30:25.093 --> 00:30:25.733
survival.

00:30:26.854 --> 00:30:27.835
rather than thriving,

00:30:29.155 --> 00:30:31.876
they have and they will continue to die

00:30:32.917 --> 00:30:34.959
with more over the next seven years than

00:30:35.660 --> 00:30:36.240
ever before.

00:30:39.396 --> 00:30:42.219
The immediate and specific fulfillment of

00:30:42.259 --> 00:30:45.700
the following pronouncement was by way of

00:30:45.880 --> 00:30:47.500
Dowd's son, Absalom,

00:30:49.321 --> 00:30:52.104
who led a devastating coup against his

00:30:52.163 --> 00:30:52.503
father,

00:30:52.544 --> 00:30:54.484
culminating with the rape of the king's

00:30:54.525 --> 00:30:55.266
concubines.

00:30:56.665 --> 00:30:57.866
But to some extent,

00:30:57.926 --> 00:31:00.909
it is also prophetic of what Sha'uwl Paul

00:31:00.949 --> 00:31:03.210
would do by replacing Dowd with his

00:31:03.269 --> 00:31:06.892
counterfeit Jesus so as to blot out the

00:31:06.951 --> 00:31:07.132
son.

00:31:12.451 --> 00:31:13.913
This is what Yahowah says.

00:31:15.615 --> 00:31:17.757
Pay attention.

00:31:17.797 --> 00:31:21.359
I will raise up against you a ra'a',

00:31:22.820 --> 00:31:24.801
a miserable, malcontent,

00:31:25.083 --> 00:31:28.025
and malignant shepherd out of your

00:31:28.085 --> 00:31:28.605
household.

00:31:30.887 --> 00:31:32.648
And I will have your women and wives

00:31:32.689 --> 00:31:36.172
taken away before your eyes and give them

00:31:36.291 --> 00:31:39.994
to your foul-mouthed and maniacal fellow

00:31:40.055 --> 00:31:40.596
countrymen.

00:31:42.098 --> 00:31:44.440
Then he will lie down with your wives

00:31:44.480 --> 00:31:49.381
and women in ayin, the sight, the eyes,

00:31:49.540 --> 00:31:54.722
and perceptions of this Shemesh sun.

00:32:00.424 --> 00:32:01.265
Throughout the Towrah,

00:32:01.545 --> 00:32:06.826
the Naby' and Mizmowr Dowd is equated to

00:32:06.846 --> 00:32:07.267
the sun,

00:32:08.767 --> 00:32:11.307
while his herald is the moon reflecting

00:32:11.407 --> 00:32:11.907
his light.

00:32:13.099 --> 00:32:14.200
But at this moment,

00:32:14.259 --> 00:32:17.040
with the assassination of 'Uwryah,

00:32:17.181 --> 00:32:18.362
the light of Yah,

00:32:19.682 --> 00:32:26.404
Yahowah's greatest luminary had quenched

00:32:26.444 --> 00:32:27.125
his energy.

00:32:29.025 --> 00:32:29.826
From the beginning,

00:32:29.846 --> 00:32:32.106
the king tried to hide his complicity,

00:32:32.146 --> 00:32:33.567
covering over his crimes,

00:32:33.606 --> 00:32:36.407
but they became so monumental that he

00:32:36.448 --> 00:32:39.028
wasn't fooling anyone but himself.

00:32:40.571 --> 00:32:42.432
God, however, is a beacon of light.

00:32:42.492 --> 00:32:43.874
Even in the darkest hours,

00:32:43.913 --> 00:32:47.356
he deals his cards face up in broad

00:32:47.396 --> 00:32:47.916
daylight.

00:32:48.597 --> 00:32:49.498
And in so doing,

00:32:50.519 --> 00:32:53.701
he is acknowledging that his son

00:32:54.162 --> 00:32:59.265
represents the son.

00:32:59.285 --> 00:33:00.986
This will be second Samuel, twelve,

00:33:01.026 --> 00:33:01.426
twelve.

00:33:03.847 --> 00:33:06.250
This is because you did this while hiding,

00:33:06.869 --> 00:33:08.872
veiled in sly secrecy.

00:33:09.912 --> 00:33:10.192
However,

00:33:10.432 --> 00:33:13.433
I will act carrying out this message in

00:33:13.473 --> 00:33:18.895
front of all Israel and before the sun.

00:33:18.935 --> 00:33:19.517
When I read that,

00:33:19.616 --> 00:33:21.198
I knew that we were doing what we

00:33:21.258 --> 00:33:24.558
needed to do.

00:33:24.638 --> 00:33:29.922
God exposed his response and his intent

00:33:31.702 --> 00:33:32.823
boldly for all to see.

00:33:32.863 --> 00:33:36.105
And in so doing,

00:33:37.627 --> 00:33:40.810
We are wise to follow his example.

00:33:41.913 --> 00:33:42.913
And we are.

00:33:45.355 --> 00:33:47.959
God had responded, had God responded,

00:33:48.038 --> 00:33:49.520
I should say, any other way,

00:33:50.961 --> 00:33:52.222
he would have also destroyed his

00:33:52.263 --> 00:33:52.884
credibility.

00:33:54.685 --> 00:33:55.026
You see,

00:33:55.067 --> 00:33:57.009
he established the parameters of the

00:33:57.048 --> 00:33:58.170
covenant in his Towrah.

00:33:59.030 --> 00:34:02.132
and now he himself must adhere to them.

00:34:02.992 --> 00:34:05.453
He cannot remain trustworthy and reliable

00:34:05.953 --> 00:34:07.214
if he alters the rules,

00:34:07.894 --> 00:34:12.036
underline life as we are living it.

00:34:12.617 --> 00:34:15.518
And so over the remaining fourteen years

00:34:16.858 --> 00:34:18.840
of his first three lives,

00:34:20.561 --> 00:34:22.740
Dowd would face the consequences of what

00:34:22.780 --> 00:34:25.882
he had done further.

00:34:27.264 --> 00:34:27.403
Well,

00:34:27.443 --> 00:34:29.525
he was right to admit that he had

00:34:29.686 --> 00:34:32.768
Chata'ah incurred the resulting guilt for

00:34:32.809 --> 00:34:35.751
having missed the way confession did not

00:34:35.811 --> 00:34:36.411
absolve him,

00:34:36.851 --> 00:34:43.376
nor will it anyone say I'm sorry after

00:34:43.456 --> 00:34:45.159
robbing a bank and killing the guard.

00:34:46.320 --> 00:34:46.420
Well,

00:34:46.460 --> 00:34:49.342
that's only going to serve to hasten and

00:34:49.382 --> 00:34:51.583
assure your conviction.

00:34:55.170 --> 00:34:59.713
So Dowd said to Nathan, I have chata'ah.

00:35:00.273 --> 00:35:02.353
I have missed the way, gone astray,

00:35:02.474 --> 00:35:05.974
and incurred the guilt and resulting loss

00:35:06.135 --> 00:35:10.635
for having been offensive against Yahowah.

00:35:10.655 --> 00:35:14.018
Shamuw'el two, twelve, thirteen in part.

00:35:14.038 --> 00:35:17.498
Well, it was an admission of guilt.

00:35:19.338 --> 00:35:22.780
It wasn't an apology.

00:35:22.860 --> 00:35:24.081
It didn't resolve the problem.

00:35:26.344 --> 00:35:27.364
Good men were dead,

00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:31.106
and an overly indulgent and irresponsible

00:35:31.146 --> 00:35:36.228
man had stolen another man's wife when he

00:35:36.268 --> 00:35:40.028
had already paid, well,

00:35:40.048 --> 00:35:42.309
he had already collected, I should say,

00:35:43.449 --> 00:35:45.630
a different one for breakfast, lunch,

00:35:45.670 --> 00:35:47.771
and dinner seven days a week.

00:35:50.351 --> 00:35:53.353
Worse, he had not only embarrassed Yahowah,

00:35:53.652 --> 00:35:54.072
who had

00:35:54.925 --> 00:35:56.266
placed so much trust in him.

00:35:57.347 --> 00:36:01.110
He had put God in a untenable position.

00:36:02.871 --> 00:36:04.873
You see, without Dowd, the sun,

00:36:05.353 --> 00:36:06.193
it doesn't shine.

00:36:07.534 --> 00:36:09.135
And all life ends on this planet.

00:36:10.456 --> 00:36:11.036
And right now,

00:36:11.097 --> 00:36:13.157
the sun was being eclipsed by a very

00:36:13.237 --> 00:36:14.978
dark and foreboding cloud.

00:36:16.239 --> 00:36:18.641
Without resolution, yeah, well, would...

00:36:20.059 --> 00:36:23.862
wouldn't be able to direct or trust his

00:36:23.922 --> 00:36:25.943
son with the fulfillment of Pesach and

00:36:25.983 --> 00:36:27.884
Matsah, resulting in Bikuwrym.

00:36:29.063 --> 00:36:31.204
Should the spring Mow'edym not be fulfilled

00:36:31.244 --> 00:36:34.567
appropriately and on schedule, well,

00:36:34.706 --> 00:36:36.367
all of the remaining would go unanswered,

00:36:36.387 --> 00:36:38.688
wouldn't they?

00:36:38.708 --> 00:36:40.369
There would be no Shabuw'ah harvest.

00:36:41.170 --> 00:36:42.409
There would be no Taruw'ah,

00:36:44.130 --> 00:36:45.431
no Kipurym homecoming,

00:36:45.592 --> 00:36:48.934
and no restoration of the planet and

00:36:48.974 --> 00:36:49.813
return to Eden.

00:36:52.827 --> 00:36:57.748
The entire human experience would be over.

00:37:01.010 --> 00:37:03.090
Fortunately, Yahowah arranged a solution.

00:37:03.710 --> 00:37:06.371
It began with a woman who would resolve

00:37:06.411 --> 00:37:09.313
the problem a woman had caused.

00:37:11.134 --> 00:37:14.014
This is the resounding and overriding

00:37:14.155 --> 00:37:16.835
message of the last word picture,

00:37:16.894 --> 00:37:18.135
the final mashal.

00:37:19.204 --> 00:37:22.447
And really it resonates throughout most

00:37:22.646 --> 00:37:24.748
all of the Mashal Proverbs.

00:37:25.608 --> 00:37:28.552
And through the Mizmowr and the Naby',

00:37:28.771 --> 00:37:31.614
the reputation of the greater luminary

00:37:31.653 --> 00:37:34.115
would be restored by the lesser luminary

00:37:34.175 --> 00:37:36.498
with the tree of knowledge pointing the

00:37:36.518 --> 00:37:38.739
way back to the tree of lives.

00:37:40.880 --> 00:37:42.963
And of a husband and wife,

00:37:43.242 --> 00:37:44.523
a mother and father working

00:37:44.563 --> 00:37:47.827
collaboratively to save their adopted son.

00:37:51.360 --> 00:37:53.581
The message Yahowah delivered through

00:37:53.621 --> 00:37:57.724
Nathan was a preemptive strike against

00:37:58.583 --> 00:38:00.965
Sha'uwl's sinister religious ploy.

00:38:02.505 --> 00:38:04.206
Dowd had buried himself,

00:38:04.547 --> 00:38:07.849
but his soul would never die.

00:38:09.190 --> 00:38:12.652
And to assure that his and ours would

00:38:12.731 --> 00:38:13.132
live,

00:38:13.211 --> 00:38:15.574
Yahowah would arrange for his son to

00:38:15.653 --> 00:38:17.635
fulfill a bar Passover.

00:38:19.425 --> 00:38:21.907
offering his Basar body as the beloved

00:38:22.007 --> 00:38:27.090
lamb of this story.

00:38:27.110 --> 00:38:29.092
The relationship would be reconciled.

00:38:29.112 --> 00:38:32.653
It reads, then Nathan replied to Dowd,

00:38:34.014 --> 00:38:34.815
nevertheless,

00:38:35.974 --> 00:38:39.717
Yahowah Abar will one day pass over your

00:38:39.797 --> 00:38:43.900
Chata guilt through your purifying

00:38:43.980 --> 00:38:44.440
offering.

00:38:46.782 --> 00:38:47.521
You will never die.

00:38:55.367 --> 00:38:58.789
laden with portent.

00:38:58.809 --> 00:38:58.909
Now,

00:38:58.929 --> 00:39:00.110
there are a couple of lessons in

00:39:00.150 --> 00:39:01.791
particular that I want to reinforce.

00:39:03.092 --> 00:39:03.353
First,

00:39:03.393 --> 00:39:05.755
while Dowd had demonstrated that he was

00:39:05.956 --> 00:39:09.197
not a perfect lamb by religious standards,

00:39:09.659 --> 00:39:12.021
it now becomes blatantly obvious that

00:39:12.041 --> 00:39:17.505
Yahowah defines tamym differently.

00:39:17.545 --> 00:39:19.186
You see, as we know,

00:39:20.407 --> 00:39:23.090
when God is speaking of the fulfillment of

00:39:23.170 --> 00:39:24.110
Pesach here,

00:39:25.333 --> 00:39:31.215
clearly stating that he's going to fulfill

00:39:31.916 --> 00:39:33.916
Pesach by interjecting a bar.

00:39:34.697 --> 00:39:35.858
That's its verbal root,

00:39:36.938 --> 00:39:38.579
and it's the answer to death.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:40.500
tamym,

00:39:40.519 --> 00:39:42.860
the word carelessly rendered perfect,

00:39:43.221 --> 00:39:46.302
has an actionable root too.

00:39:46.342 --> 00:39:48.083
Just like a bar is the actionable root

00:39:48.103 --> 00:39:50.304
of Pesach, it is tamym,

00:39:51.005 --> 00:39:52.445
and it speaks of finishing,

00:39:52.945 --> 00:39:53.965
not of being flawless.

00:39:55.188 --> 00:39:58.130
of completing the mission rather than

00:39:58.251 --> 00:40:03.675
standing idly by and not occurring guilt.

00:40:03.695 --> 00:40:04.195
Therefore,

00:40:04.255 --> 00:40:08.579
Dowd became the tamym lamb when he

00:40:08.719 --> 00:40:12.342
re-engaged after re-establishing his

00:40:12.742 --> 00:40:14.324
relationship with Yahowah and earning

00:40:14.364 --> 00:40:15.025
Yahowah's trust.

00:40:16.168 --> 00:40:18.630
completing his calling by fulfilling Chag

00:40:18.650 --> 00:40:19.110
Matsah.

00:40:19.710 --> 00:40:23.172
When his Basar body was sacrificed as the

00:40:23.213 --> 00:40:23.532
lamb,

00:40:23.572 --> 00:40:25.653
he opened the door to eternal life for

00:40:25.695 --> 00:40:28.295
himself in addition to the rest of us.

00:40:29.376 --> 00:40:30.376
And then on Matsah,

00:40:30.436 --> 00:40:32.759
when his nepesh soul carried our guilt

00:40:32.818 --> 00:40:36.019
into Sheowl to make us innocent before God,

00:40:37.041 --> 00:40:38.922
he was also carrying and offloading his

00:40:39.041 --> 00:40:41.744
own.

00:40:41.764 --> 00:40:45.045
The resolution that Yahowah had established

00:40:45.891 --> 00:40:48.833
in the Towrah applied to the Bikuwr,

00:40:49.012 --> 00:40:49.753
the firstborn,

00:40:51.153 --> 00:40:52.775
as well as to other Bikuwrym,

00:40:53.175 --> 00:40:54.094
firstborn children.

00:40:55.096 --> 00:40:56.677
God didn't change the rule.

00:40:57.836 --> 00:40:59.038
He applied them.

00:41:00.438 --> 00:41:01.259
And with Dowd,

00:41:01.978 --> 00:41:04.920
Yahowah enabled the benefits.

00:41:07.402 --> 00:41:09.123
It is an amazing story.

